main event: A sighting of four objects in the Seattle area on May 6, 1960, which were later determined to be reflections of street lights.
interesting points: The witness submitted photographs that were analyzed, revealing that the lights were reflections through a window,The objects were noted to be stationary in the sky,The weather was clear, allowing for better visibility during the observation,The witness experienced difficulty obtaining clear photographs due to the conditions,Official analysis concluded that the sightings were an attempt to pass off reflections as UFOs.
sighted object: four stationary lights in the sky
witness description: An individual who used binoculars and a camera to capture the images.
